title: Two-fingered salute from NZ comic Tape Face shocks UK morning TV viewers
text:
Two-fingered salute from NZ comic Tape Face shocks UK morning TV viewers Last updated 11:56, February 4 2017 THIS MORNING/SCREENGRAB 
Tape Face's real name is Sam Wills. 
It's safe to say New Zealand comedian Tape Face got the viewers of UK show This Morning talking. 
The comic, who reached the finals of America's Got Talent , flashed a V sign while performing one of his routines on the show. 
That didn't sit well with some viewers and they let the show know about it. THIS MORNING/SCREENGRAB 
The offending two-fingered salute which shocked some viewers. 
One even said the act was "disgusting ... swearing before watershed."
